(1) Before approving registration, the Registrar may require such additional information about the proposed society as he deems necessary, including— (a) the economic or other need for the organisation of the society ; (b) the educational and advisory work respecting co-operative principles and the organisaton and operations already being carried on amongst the applicants for registration and other persons expected to become members; (c) the number of persons expected to become members upon the commencement of operations; (d) whether the capital to be furnished initially by the applicants for registration and other persons expected to become members is sufficient for the commencement of operations; (e) the availability of officers capable of directing and managing the affairs of the society , and of keeping such records and books of account for the society as the Registrar may require.
