(1) A society may be registered primarily for the purpose of providing farming services to its members, including— (a) purchasing, taking on lease or otherwise acquiring, developing, maintaining and operating land as a farming enterprise on behalf of its members; or (b) purchasing; taking on lease or otherwise acquiring land for farming purposes and using such land by— (i) dividing a portion thereof amongst its members, by sale, lease or otherwise, for their individual use and operation as producers of agricultural products; and (ii) developing, maintaining and operating the remainder of such land as a farming enterprise on behalf of its members.
